<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 28 at 5:49PM CDT until July 28 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Oldham County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hartley County in the Panhandle of Texas...
* Until 615 PM CDT.
* At 549 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 5 miles northwest
of Boys Ranch, or 24 miles north of Vega, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
* Locations impacted include...
Channing and Boys Ranch.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
